text:
{
  "prompt": "A 3D concept illustration of a futuristic electric motorcycle (e-motorbike) featuring a skate-board style battery pack integrated under the chassis. The air intake begins at the front fairing, flows through a tunnel above the battery (under the seat), and exits toward the rear and underbody. The battery is housed in a flat aerodynamic shell (aero cowling). The rear motor is connected to a 5-speed automatic gearbox, with belt drive to the rear wheel. The design includes front and rear wheels, a compact seat above the tunnel, aerodynamic body fairings, and highlighted airflow direction using arrows. The overall structure is compact and designed for city delivery use, showing airflow dynamics and energy-efficient structure. Include color-coded components: red battery tunnel, blue airflow arrows, black frame and seat, yellow wheels, and purple motor/controller block.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A technical side cutaway illustration of an electric motorcycle with a fully aerodynamic air tunnel running straight from the front to the rear. The image shows air intake at the front fairing, passing through a hollow chassis where the battery pack is flat and low (skateboard style), and exiting at the tail section. The motor is positioned low and compact, allowing for an uninterrupted air tunnel. The cutaway reveals airflow lines in blue to show smooth passage from front to back. The motorcycle has a futuristic design with aerodynamic fairings.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "An advanced electric scooter-style motorcycle with a fully integrated front-to-rear air tunnel. The scooter has a step-through frame, low seat with a PCX-style comfortable backrest, and footrests on both sides of a central aerodynamic air duct. The air intake is located at the front fairing, flowing straight through a hollow central tunnel that sits above a flat skateboard-style battery pack mounted low in the chassis. The rear features an aerodynamic tail section where the air exits. The motor and 5-speed automatic transmission are mounted at the rear, with a belt drive to the wide rear tire. The overall design is sleek, futuristic, with aerodynamic lines flowing from front to rear. Highlight airflow lines with blue arrows showing cooling flow from front intake to rear exhaust. High detail, side perspective, realistic render.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A conceptual 3D-rendered electric scooter with a Harley-style low seat and low ground clearance. The rider's legs are spread to both sides in cruiser-style riding posture. A large, straight central air tunnel passes completely through the center of the frame from the front to the rear. The battery pack is a skateboard-style flat battery mounted beneath the main frame. The frame integrates the tunnel, and the overall design is aerodynamic and functional. The front and rear wheels are exposed, and the front has an air intake integrated into a minimalist aerodynamic fairing. The design is futuristic but grounded in real-world mechanical feasibility.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A futuristic electric scooter concept with a fully integrated aerodynamic design. The body features a large, straight-through air tunnel starting from the front intake and exiting at the rear, running in a clean horizontal line through the core frame. The seat is suspended above this tunnel, and the rider's legs rest to the sides of the open airflow path. The front and rear wheels are streamlined into the design. The body has a matte metallic gray color with minimalist details. The overall design is sleek, aerodynamic, and optimized for high efficiency. The airflow path is clearly visible as a tunnel cut through the frame.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 2D side-view concept sketch of an electric scooter with a straight air tunnel running through the center from front to rear. The scooter features a low Harley-style seating position, with the rider's legs spread on both sides of the air tunnel. The overall frame is slim and aerodynamic, and the air tunnel acts as both structural frame and airflow channel. The scooter includes handlebars, wheels, seat, and minimalistic fairings. A human figure is seated on it to show ergonomic riding posture. The sketch should be technical and functional, in monochrome pencil or blueprint style.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A side-view technical concept sketch (2D line drawing) of an electric scooter featuring a straight horizontal air tunnel that runs from the front to the rear of the vehicle. The frame design resembles a Harley-style low-rider with wide, low footrests, and the rider's legs are spread to the sides of the frame. The air tunnel is a fully unobstructed straight line, running through the center of the scooter, underneath a low-profile seat mounted on top of the frame. The overall design emphasizes aerodynamic efficiency and structural simplicity. The drawing should clearly show the structural frame, the air tunnel path, and the seat position, with emphasis on technical clarity and feasibility.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 2D technical side-profile line drawing of an electric motorcycle designed with an integrated straight-through air tunnel frame. The frame is constructed using aluminum alloy (6061-T6), with a large tubular structure running from the front intake below the headlight through the seat base to the rear exhaust outlet. The air tunnel doubles as the main load-bearing structure of the motorcycle. The design includes a low seat height similar to cruiser-style motorcycles (not PCX style), with foot placement slightly forward and legs spread apart. The battery pack is mounted as a skateboard-style unit under the tunnel. The handlebars, front fork, rear swingarm, and motor are sketched, but the focus is on the frame and airflow tunnel. The drawing should clearly depict airflow arrows and use engineering-style clarity with visible weld joints, tubing diameter, and component labeling in grayscale lines.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A technical 2D side profile concept sketch of an electric scooter with a central aerodynamic air tunnel running in a straight line from the front intake to the rear exhaust. The frame of the scooter integrates the tunnel as a structural element, made from aluminum. The rider sits in a cruiser-style low riding position, with legs spread on either side of the tunnel. The battery pack is located beneath the tunnel in a skateboard-style flat configuration. The overall design is aerodynamic and minimalist, with smooth surfaces and integrated components. Include simple annotations like 'Front Air Intake', 'Air Tunnel', 'Battery Pack', and 'Rear Exhaust'.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A detailed 2D sectional technical drawing of an electric motorcycle concept. The frame is designed with a skateboard-style integrated battery pack (96V 300Ah), and a straight-line air tunnel flows from the front intake to the rear exhaust. The rider's legs straddle the structure, similar to a cruiser bike (Harley-style). The drawing shows a cross-sectional side view with annotations: low center of gravity battery pack at the bottom, straight airflow tunnel running above it, reinforced aluminum frame structure, and aerodynamic casing. The air tunnel is fully integrated into the frame and flows unobstructed from front to rear. Minimalistic, technical illustration style with black linework and white background, suitable for engineering visualization.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A concept electric scooter with an aerodynamic air tunnel design. The air intake begins at the front sides and is split into left and right channels that route around the seat area, with visible air outlets near the rear wheel sides. The scooter features a comfortable upright riding position, step-through frame, and integrated battery in the footboard. The frame is made of matte aluminum and the overall look is sleek and modern. It should prioritize both airflow and rider ergonomics, resembling a practical city commuter scooter, not a race bike.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A technical concept sketch (2D line drawing) of an electric touring motorcycle inspired by the BMW R1250RT police bike, but without a fuel tank or muffler. The seat is deep and contoured like a touring bike, with a relaxed riding posture. Instead of a fuel tank, a flat top deck integrates seamlessly into the chassis. An aerodynamic front fairing with a tall windshield guides airflow into internal ducts. The battery pack is shaped like a skateboard deck and integrated into the lower frame. The motorcycle includes a fully electric powertrain and side-mounted storage boxes. The frame is designed with airflow tunnels guiding air from the front intake to the rear, with visible airflow paths. Rider shown seated comfortably in touring position. Sketch is technical and clean, side view.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 2D side-profile digital line sketch of an electric motorcycle with a low seat height and ergonomic urban riding geometry. The seat is set very low, allowing for full foot contact with the ground. The rider's leg position shows a knee angle of about 100–110 degrees, with footrests positioned slightly forward and upward. The motorcycle features a flat skateboard-style battery pack integrated under the seat area. A large air tunnel runs straight through the center of the frame from the front intake to rear exhaust. The overall design is sleek, functional, and optimized for urban stop-and-go delivery usage.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A high-quality side profile rendering of a PCX-style electric scooter with a fully integrated aerodynamic airflow tunnel. The scooter has a modern, sleek body similar to Honda PCX, but with a unique design that includes a visible front air intake and a rear air outlet forming a straight airflow channel through the middle of the vehicle. The airflow tunnel is a structural part of the aluminum or chromoly frame. The seat is low and comfortable, with the rider's knee angle at around 100-110 degrees. The footrest is clearly visible and ergonomically placed. The overall design is practical for city commuting but emphasizes aerodynamic efficiency.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 2D side-view technical concept drawing of a modern electric scooter inspired by the PCX design. The scooter features a rider in a comfortable upright position with a knee angle between 100 to 110 degrees. The design includes a wide front air intake integrated into the front cowling, tapering into a narrow, directed air tunnel that runs through the center frame of the scooter and exits at the rear. The tunnel serves both as a cooling and aerodynamic feature. The seat is positioned low, and there are visible footrests allowing natural leg placement. The overall design is sleek, aerodynamic, and practical for city commuting.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A technical 2D cross-sectional side-view illustration of an electric scooter design. The scooter features an integrated lower structure that includes a battery pack, electric motor, and aerodynamic air duct system. The air duct begins with a wide front intake and narrows toward the rear exhaust, forming a smooth tunnel below the seat platform. The total ground clearance is 600mm. The overall frame is compact and streamlined, similar to a modern PCX scooter. The air tunnel is visually highlighted, showing the airflow path from front to back through the integrated duct. The design includes a low seat, a rider footrest with a knee angle of about 100 to 110 degrees, and a visible step-over platform. The background is neutral gray with clean technical rendering lines.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A detailed 2D technical side-view drawing of the lower part of an electric scooter. The image focuses only on the motor, battery, and integrated air tunnel. The motor is placed near the rear wheel, the battery is a rectangular pack mounted horizontally along the scooter's floor, and the air tunnel flows from the front intake around or over the battery and exits toward the rear, clearly marked with blue arrows. The design is clean, technical, and uses black linework with minimal shading on a light background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A schematic digital illustration on a light beige background showing only the motor, battery, and air tunnel system of an electric scooter. The design eliminates airflow directed toward the ground. The air enters from the wide front intake and flows through a streamlined tunnel, bypassing the underside and exiting through a narrow rear outlet above the motor and battery compartment. The layout is minimalistic and technical, highlighting functional components without wheels, frame, or seating.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A technical 2D side-profile digital illustration of an electric scooter motorcycle with a straight-through air tunnel. The tunnel starts at the front intake vent, passes through a flat module containing the battery and motor, and exits at the rear of the bike. The airflow is strictly horizontal from front to rear, with no downward flow. The air tunnel is integrated into the frame as a structural component. The seat is positioned above the tunnel, and the rider's feet rest on either side of the tunnel. The ground clearance is 600mm, and the design emphasizes aerodynamic efficiency. The illustration is line-drawn in a minimalist, blueprint-like style on a clean background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A detailed 2D technical line drawing (side view) of a high-performance electric motorcycle with a flat, skateboard-style battery pack mounted as a single-layer slab under the rider's foot platform. The battery pack is wide (approximately 600mm) and flat, extending lengthwise along the lower chassis. Air intake is visible at the front, flowing through a tunnel integrated into the frame and exiting at the rear. The motor is mounted at the rear end of the battery pack, connected to a 5-speed mechanical transmission and belt-drive to the rear wheel. The design omits the traditional fuel tank and exhaust, with a low seat and slightly reclined rider position. Emphasis on mechanical clarity and energy flow direction. No colors, just clean technical lines on a white background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A conceptual 3D-rendered side-view of a modern electric scooter with a skateboard-style battery pack at the bottom acting as the structural base for all components. The battery pack is wide (600mm), flat, and runs the full length of the vehicle base. Above it, the seat, motor, and aerodynamic air duct components are mounted. The air tunnel starts wide at the front and tapers at the rear, integrated into the main body. The design should have a minimalist and futuristic aesthetic, suitable for urban mobility. Include handlebars, mirrors, and wheels. The riding posture is low and comfortable.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A conceptual 3D rendering of a minimalistic 20-inch electric kick scooter designed for high capacity and performance. It features a long, wide skateboard-style deck housing a single-layer 96V 300Ah battery pack. The deck serves as the structural base for all components. The frame is bare and functional, without decorative cowlings. The front and rear wheels are 20-inch, with a robust fork and rear motor assembly. The design emphasizes utility and performance, with exposed components and a sleek, industrial aesthetic. Side view, light background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A conceptual 3D-rendered electric scooter with a minimalist design, featuring a 20-inch front wheel and a 16-inch rear wheel. The scooter has full suspension on both wheels and a low-profile padded saddle installed. The design includes a large, flat battery pack at the base, acting as the frame for mounting all components, resembling a skateboard deck. The structure is open with no body panels or fairings, and components like the motor and controllers are visibly mounted to the underside. The scooter has bicycle-style handlebars and a sturdy, compact structure suitable for high-capacity commuting.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A technical 2D side-profile digital line drawing of a conceptual high-power electric scooter with the following specifications: it features a 96V 300Ah single-layer battery pack integrated as the structural base platform. The battery pack measures 600mm wide and approximately 1200mm long, forming the main frame of the vehicle. The scooter has a 20-inch front wheel and a 16-inch rear wheel, both with full suspension (front and rear shocks). It has a very low saddle mounted directly above the rear suspension, and wide footrests that are flush with the battery pack. The motor is integrated into the rear wheel hub, and the design does not include any exterior fairings or cowls — only a minimalistic frame, saddle, wheels, suspension, and battery. The drawing is clean, monochrome, and blueprint-style on a white background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 3D-rendered concept of an electric scooter with a kickboard-style lower frame housing a large battery (96V 300Ah). Attached to this base is a seat frame structure, with a full-size padded seat mounted on it. The rear of the seat frame has dual rear suspension (dual shocks) connecting to a 16-inch rear wheel. The front has a 20-inch wheel with suspension forks. The entire vehicle has a raw, functional design with no decorative cowlings, emphasizing utility and structural visibility. Matte metal and exposed components.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 2D technical side-profile sketch of a fully faired electric scooter designed for ultra-long range. The design includes a low-slung aerodynamic shell with a continuous airflow tunnel from front to back, a transparent canopy roof, fully enclosed wheels, and a single-layer skateboard-style battery pack integrated into the floorboard. The rider sits in a reclined cruiser-style position, with rear dual suspension and small air intakes at the front and a tapered aerodynamic tail. The entire vehicle has a sleek, futuristic, velomobile-inspired shape, drawn in clean black-and-white technical line art style.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 3D-rendered digital image of an ultra-aerodynamic electric scooter designed for long range, featuring a roofed fairing, fully enclosed body, and extremely low rolling resistance. The scooter includes a seat, front 20-inch wheel, rear 16-inch wheel, and dual rear suspension. A person is seated on the scooter, wearing casual riding attire, sitting in a relaxed position. The background is neutral and minimal to focus on the vehicle and rider. The design emphasizes low drag and compactness, suitable for urban commuting.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A futuristic electric scooter with an aerodynamic canopy and ultra-low drag design. The vehicle features a skateboard-style base housing a 96V 300Ah battery pack. The wheelbase has been extended significantly to allow for a more reclined rider posture with stretched legs. A realistic human model is seated on the scooter with legs comfortably extended, showcasing the relaxed riding geometry. The front wheel is 20 inches and the rear wheel is 16 inches, both equipped with full suspension. The design is minimalistic with no external fairings except the aerodynamic canopy, and the color scheme is metallic silver and black.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A futuristic electric scooter concept with an extended wheelbase of 2 meters. The vehicle features a low-profile aerodynamic canopy that covers the rider, designed to minimize air resistance. The rider is sitting in a laid-back, feet-forward position similar to a cruiser motorcycle. The front wheel is 20 inches and the rear wheel is 16 inches, both with full suspension. The battery pack is housed in a skateboard-like flat base that forms the structural chassis of the vehicle. The scooter is minimalistic, without decorative fairings. The background is a clean, neutral studio environment to emphasize the vehicle design.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A technical side-view drawing of a futuristic electric scooter with a long 1700mm wheelbase. The vehicle features a fully integrated skateboard-style single-layer 96V 300Ah battery base, with a seated rider in a relaxed position. The seat is low, and the footrest is wide and positioned for a comfortable knee angle of about 100-110 degrees. The design includes full front and rear suspension, aerodynamic form without bulky cowls, and a narrow rear with a built-in cargo rack. The scooter has a 20-inch front wheel and a 16-inch rear wheel, both visible in profile.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 3D-rendered digital image of a streamlined electric scooter with an aerodynamic canopy and a wheelbase of 1700mm. The rider's pelvis is positioned 200mm higher than in the previous version, resulting in a more upright riding posture. The design features a large flat battery deck (96V 300Ah), front 20-inch and rear 16-inch wheels, and a fully enclosed aerodynamic fairing. The scooter includes integrated rear suspension and optimized air ducting for reduced drag. The environment is a clean studio background with good lighting.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A futuristic electric scooter with a sleek aerodynamic design. The vehicle has a fully enclosed body with a transparent canopy-like windshield. The rider sits inside, with a low and relaxed posture. The front wheel is 20 inches, the rear wheel is 16 inches, and the wheelbase is approximately 1700mm. The lower chassis is a flat, extended battery pack like a skateboard deck, with integrated air ducts for cooling. The overall design is elegant, modern, and minimal, with clean lines and a visually balanced silhouette. The scooter is shown in a matte white and silver color scheme, under natural daylight on a city street.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A futuristic electric delivery scooter designed with a streamlined, functional look, inspired by the naked sports bike shown in the previous photo. It features a single central rear suspension mounted horizontally beneath the seat frame, a long and low-profile battery pack integrated into the floorboard, front 20-inch and rear 16-inch wheels with full suspension, a wide and low rider seat with a separate frame, and a compact rear cargo box mount. The overall shape resembles a hybrid between a scooter and a naked motorcycle, optimized for high-efficiency delivery use. Minimal body panels, exposed mechanical structure, and a slightly aggressive yet practical design. High-resolution side view.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}
